---
import CImage from '@components/c-Image/index.astro';
import CText from '@components/c-Text/index.astro';
import SExample from '@sections/s-Example/index.astro';
import Layout from '@layouts/layout.astro';

import testImage from '@images/test.jpg';

const title = "about nine:am"
const description = "An opinionated framework for Astro."
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
	<CText>
		<h2 class="ft-h1">
			The day leaned softly against the edge of time, unhurried and golden. Shadows stretched across the ground like thoughts that never found words. A bird called out once, as if to remind the world it was still listening. In that quiet, something simple took root — not a dream, but the space that allows one to grow.
		</h2>
		<br/>
		<p>– Edge of Time</p>
	</CText>
	<SExample title="About">
		<p>
			The air carried a soft hum of distant traffic and the faint clatter of dishes from a nearby café. Somewhere, a window creaked open and let in the scent of rain just beginning to fall. It wasn’t a moment anyone would remember, but it held a quiet weight — the kind that lives between one thought and the next. The day unfolded slowly, not in bursts of purpose, but in small, unhurried gestures. And somehow, that was enough.
    	</p>
	</SExample>
	<CImage src={testImage} />
</Layout>
